# v3.18.0 PATCH: normalize line endings to LF
#
# Background: The repo's local config has `core.eol=lf` but no
# `.gitattributes` enforcement. When a developer on Windows (default
# CRLF in many editors) commits a file, git stores CRLF in the index.
# Future merges against files that were committed with LF then treat
# every line as a whitespace conflict, producing 12-file merge bombs
# even when content is byte-identical.
#
# This file normalizes line endings on commit (LF for text) while
# preserving CRLF in working trees where it's intentional (none, for
# this repo).
#
# Symptom this fixes: `git merge` produces conflict markers spanning
# hundreds of lines on files where HEAD=CRLF and origin/main=LF.

# Default: detect text/binary automatically, normalize to LF on commit
* text=auto eol=lf

# Force LF for code files even if some tool misclassifies them
*.cs text eol=lf
*.csproj text eol=lf
*.props text eol=lf
*.targets text eol=lf
*.sln text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.xml text eol=lf
*.xaml text eol=lf
*.cshtml text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf

# Binary files (explicit, just to be safe)
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.dll binary
*.exe binary
*.pdb binary
*.zip binary
*.pdf binary